underlying_goal: Commit a large, heterogeneous set of changes into logically distinct commits.
primary_success: Correctly identified several logically distinct changes within a large set of modified files and expertly separated them into multiple, well-described commits, including interactively handling untracked files with the user.
brief_summary: The user initiated a commit for a large number of changes. The agent analyzed the changes, identified three logically separate groups (documentation, prompt library expansion, and a code fix), and created three commits. After interactively confirming with the user, it added remaining untracked files in a fourth commit, successfully organizing the complex changeset.
